2
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:33,400
みんなの主食だよ。
It's everyone's staple food.

3
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,400
ご飯食べないと走れなくなる、みんな忘れないでよ。
If you don't eat, you won't be able to run. Don't forget, everyone!

4
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:39,100
やべえ！ それ基本ね！
Crap! That's basic stuff!

5
00:01:39,500 --> 00:01:41,500
基本、基本。
Basic, basic.

6
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:44,200
ちょっと聞こえづらい？わたための声。
Is Watame's voice a bit hard to hear?

7
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:47,300
わー！
Yay!

8
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:54,000
あ、あ、あ、あ！
Ah, ah, ah, ah!

9
00:01:57,000 --> 00:01:59,000
馬鹿にしてんのか！？あ、あ、あ！
Are you making fun of me?! Ah, ah, ah!

10
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:09,500
うわ、スバルちゃん待って、なんかハイレグだよ。
Whoa, wait, Subaru-chan, you're wearing a high-leg leotard.

11
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:11,800
バニーじゃん。 ハイレグやめて！
It's a bunny suit. Stop with the high-leg!

12
00:02:14,000 --> 00:02:18,500
いや、間違ってないでしょ！わたためは黄色ハイレグで、スバルは黒ハイレグ！
I mean, I'm not wrong! Watame is wearing yellow, and Subaru is in black!

13
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
みんな、どっちがセクシー？どっちがセクシー？
Everyone, which one is sexier? Which one is sexier?

14
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:30,500
スバルか、わたためか、どっち？
Subaru or Watame, which one?

15
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:38,000
いや、やっぱりバニガかな、スバル。
Nah, definitely bunny girl, Subaru.

16
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,500
バニーガールには誰も勝てない。
No one can beat a bunny girl.

17
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:45,000
見せればいいってもんじゃないよ。
It's not just about showing it off.

18
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:49,000
バニーガールって言っても、わたためのことだからね。
Even if you say bunny girl, that refers to Watame, you know.

19
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,500
え、スバルは？ / スバルちゃんは...
Eh, what about Subaru? / Subaru-chan is...

20
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:00,800
ボタアン！
Botan!

21
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:12,000
みんなの声300%にしてみた。
I turned everyone's volume up to 300%.

22
00:03:13,500 --> 00:03:16,500
300？300はでかいね。
300? 300 is huge.

23
00:03:19,500 --> 00:03:22,500
これ以上上げられないくらい上げてる。
I raised it as much as possible.

24
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:35,000
こんちくわー！
Konchikuwa!

25
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,000
りおな！りおな！
Riona! Riona!

26
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:51,000
もう、刃物どもは終わり散らかしてる。
Those blades are running completely amok.

27
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:02,000
スバルボイス、みんな、音量...
Subaru's voice, everyone's volume...

28
00:04:02,000 --> 00:04:04,500
あ、聞こえてる？
Ah, can you hear me?

29
00:04:07,000 --> 00:04:10,000
ビビ！こんばんは！
Vivi! Good evening!

30
00:04:13,000 --> 00:04:16,000
ビビ、こんばんは！ / あ、聞こえない？
Vivi, good evening! / Ah, you can't hear?

31
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,000
あ、ビビちゃん聞こえない？
Ah, Vivi-chan, I can't hear you?

32
00:04:20,500 --> 00:04:23,000
聞こえてますか？
Can you hear me?

33
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:26,500
あ！聞こえてるよ！
Ah! I can hear you!

34
00:04:26,500 --> 00:04:28,000
あ、聞こえてた！
Ah, you could hear me!

35
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:32,000
今なら歌を歌ってもバレない。
Even if I sing right now, nobody will find out.

36
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:36,000
よし、ビビ！
Alright, Vivi!

37
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,000
イェーイ！
Yay!

38
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:47,000
しらけん、みんな面白い。
Shiraken, everyone is so funny.

39
00:05:00,008 --> 00:05:02,008
静かにしたほうがいいのかな？
Should we be quiet?

40
00:05:02,008 --> 00:05:05,108
聞こえる？聞こえる？こっちちっちゃい？
Can you hear me? Can you hear me? Is my voice too quiet?

41
00:05:05,108 --> 00:05:08,508
これ、大きくしたほうがいい？
Should I turn it up?

42
00:05:08,508 --> 00:05:10,508
あ、なんかベビィに似合ってるよ。
Oh, it looks good on you, baby.

43
00:05:10,508 --> 00:05:13,008
大丈夫？
Is it okay?

44
00:05:13,008 --> 00:05:15,808
聞こえますか？
Can you hear me?

45
00:05:15,808 --> 00:05:19,408
アキちゃんも似合ってる。
It suits Aki-chan too.

46
00:05:19,408 --> 00:05:22,008
はーい。
Okay.

47
00:05:22,008 --> 00:05:25,508
じゃあ、ちょっと説明、はい、します。
Alright, then I'll briefly explain things.

48
00:05:25,508 --> 00:05:27,508
と言っても簡潔にしますね。
Though I'll keep it concise.

49
00:05:27,508 --> 00:05:29,808
今日、ありがとうございます。
Thank you all for joining today.

50
00:05:29,808 --> 00:05:33,208
ちょっと1時間、遅く始まってるんで...
Since we started about an hour late...

51
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:38,208
終了時間が今日1時までとなっておりますが、退出は自由なので...
today's end time will be 1:00 AM, but you can leave whenever...

52
00:05:38,208 --> 00:05:41,208
何かご用事ある方は、あの、適宜抜けても大丈夫です。
so if you have other things to do, you can leave as needed.

53
00:05:41,208 --> 00:05:43,008
はーい。
Okay.

54
00:05:43,008 --> 00:05:47,808
で、えーと、普段、あの、株のルーレット、本来だったら21時から回してたんですが...
Also, normally we would spin the stock roulette starting from 9:00 PM...

55
00:05:47,808 --> 00:05:52,508
1時間遅れているので、えーと、22時スタートになります。
but since we're an hour behind, it will start at 10:00 PM today.

56
00:05:52,508 --> 00:05:54,808
おーい。/ はーい。
Okay.

57
00:05:54,808 --> 00:05:59,808
で、そこから、はい、1時間ごとに、今日は22時、23時、24時に...
And from then, yes, every hour, today we will spin it at 10:00, 11:00, and 12:00...

58
00:05:59,808 --> 00:06:04,208
の3回回すことになりますので、あの、株手に入れたい方は...
for a total of three spins. So if you want to get stocks...

59
00:06:04,208 --> 00:06:08,508
えー、22時までに、まあ、ちょっと持っとくと、第1回目のルーレットが間に合うかなと思います。
if you have some by 10:00 PM, I think you'll make it in time for the first spin.

60
00:06:08,508 --> 00:06:11,508
はーい。
Okay.

61
00:06:11,508 --> 00:06:15,508
はい。で、職業の振り方は、その目の前の、あの、受付...
Yes. And as for distributing your job points, at the reception desk in front of you...

62
00:06:15,508 --> 00:06:18,508
スキル受付の場所があるんですが...
where you can assign skills...

63
00:06:18,508 --> 00:06:21,008
今日だけ、あの、リセット何回でもできます。
only for today, you can reset your points as many times as you want.

64
00:06:21,008 --> 00:06:24,008
明日からは、1日1回なので。
From tomorrow on, it'll only be once a day.

65
00:06:24,008 --> 00:06:27,508
はい。今日終了する際の、あの、職とか...
Yes. Your jobs when we wrap up today...

66
00:06:27,508 --> 00:06:31,508
多分引き継ぎになるのかな？またちょっと後で連絡はしますが、お気をつけください。
will probably carry over. I'll contact you later about it, but please keep that in mind.

67
00:06:31,508 --> 00:06:35,508
明日は1日1回です。
Tomorrow, it's only once a day.

68
00:06:35,508 --> 00:06:38,208
なんか、なんかゴーゴーゴーって言ってる。
There's some roaring background noise.

69
00:06:38,208 --> 00:06:42,508
ハウリングしてるかも。
It might be audio feedback.

70
00:06:42,508 --> 00:06:45,008
はい、スピーカーが。
Yeah, the speaker.

71
00:06:45,008 --> 00:06:48,508
で、あの、もし、何か分からないことあったら、もう気軽に呼んでください。
And if there's anything you don't understand, feel free to call me.

72
00:06:48,508 --> 00:06:51,508
すぐ私向かえるんで、はい。
I can head over to help right away.

73
00:06:51,508 --> 00:06:54,508
はーい。
Okay.

74
00:06:54,508 --> 00:06:58,008
来てくれなかったら文功言っていいんですか？
Can we complain if you don't show up?

75
00:06:58,008 --> 00:07:00,808
文功言ってもいいけどさー...
I mean, you can complain, but...

76
00:07:00,808 --> 00:07:05,508
その後のこと考えろよ。大丈夫か？
you better think about the consequences. Got it?

77
00:07:05,508 --> 00:07:09,508
おどしてる。
She's threatening us.

78
00:07:09,508 --> 00:07:14,208
じゃあ、あと本当に何か分からないことあったり、困ったことあったら気軽に呼んでください。
So again, if you really don't understand something or get stuck, feel free to call.

79
00:07:14,208 --> 00:07:17,508
はーい。
Okay.

80
00:07:17,508 --> 00:07:21,008
では、以上です。もう、はい、散り散り、無職ども。行け行け。
Alright, that's all. Now disperse, you jobless folks. Go, go!

81
00:07:21,008 --> 00:07:25,808
行こう行こう！
Let's go, let's go!

82
00:07:25,808 --> 00:07:28,208
ダンジョンなの？
Is it a dungeon?

83
00:07:28,208 --> 00:07:31,008
職業振り分け。
Job assignment.

84
00:07:31,008 --> 00:07:35,008
振り分け係。
Assignment clerk.

85
00:07:35,008 --> 00:07:37,008
どっち？
Which one?

86
00:07:37,008 --> 00:07:41,508
職業...
Jobs...

87
00:07:41,508 --> 00:07:43,508
ファーマー？
Farmer?

88
00:07:43,508 --> 00:07:46,508
職業振り分け。
Job assignment.

89
00:07:46,508 --> 00:07:49,008
ファーマーかな？
Maybe Farmer?

90
00:07:49,008 --> 00:07:51,508
ファーマー？
Farmer?

91
00:07:51,508 --> 00:07:54,508
ファーマーにしよう。
I'll go with Farmer.

92
00:07:54,508 --> 00:07:58,508
ファーマー10。
Farmer 10.

93
00:07:58,508 --> 00:08:02,508
ファーマー。
Farmer.

94
00:08:02,508 --> 00:08:04,208
ギャンブラー？
Gambler?

95
00:08:04,208 --> 00:08:07,508
今日振れるの？
Can we assign them today?

96
00:08:07,508 --> 00:08:09,508
私は...
I'll...

97
00:08:09,508 --> 00:08:12,508
ファーマー。
Farmer.

98
00:08:12,508 --> 00:08:15,508
ファーマーか。
Farmer, I guess.

99
00:08:15,508 --> 00:08:19,508
アルケミスト、かっこいい名前。
Alchemist is a cool name.

100
00:08:19,508 --> 00:08:22,008
あ、オッケー。
Ah, okay.

101
00:08:22,008 --> 00:08:25,508
アルケミスト。
Alchemist.

102
00:08:25,508 --> 00:08:27,808
私はアルケミスト。
I'll be an Alchemist.

103
00:08:27,808 --> 00:08:31,008
アリーナ？
Arena?

104
00:08:31,008 --> 00:08:34,508
一旦、ファーマー。
For now, Farmer.

105
00:08:34,508 --> 00:08:37,508
バトルダンジョンも...
Battle dungeon is also...

106
00:08:37,508 --> 00:08:41,208
パズル？
Puzzle?

107
00:08:41,208 --> 00:08:44,208
パズルやってみよう。
Let's try puzzle.

108
00:08:44,208 --> 00:08:48,508
パズル。
Puzzle.

109
00:08:48,508 --> 00:08:52,508
ファイター10にしといて、振り直せるんだよね。
I'll put 10 into Fighter, we can reset them later anyway.

110
00:08:52,508 --> 00:08:55,208
アスレイベント。
Athletic event.

111
00:08:55,208 --> 00:08:58,208
アスレイベント。
Athletic event.

112
00:08:58,208 --> 00:09:02,008
アスレチックとミニゲーム。
Athletic and mini-games.

113
00:09:02,008 --> 00:09:07,508
ミニゲーム。
Mini-games.

114
00:09:07,508 --> 00:09:10,508
道具。
Tools.

115
00:09:10,508 --> 00:09:13,008
これ、どうやって買うの？
How do we buy things?

116
00:09:13,008 --> 00:09:15,508
イナ。
Ina.

117
00:09:15,508 --> 00:09:18,508
イナの頭。
Ina's head.

118
00:09:18,508 --> 00:09:22,008
オッケー、とりあえず探してみよう。どこにあるのか。
Okay, let's just figure out where everything is.

119
00:09:22,008 --> 00:09:24,508
あ、ここ？
Oh, here?

120
00:09:24,508 --> 00:09:30,008
釣り。
Fishing.

121
00:09:30,008 --> 00:09:32,208
釣り。
Fishing.

122
00:09:32,208 --> 00:09:35,008
フリーマーケット。
Free market.

123
00:09:35,008 --> 00:09:38,208
まだ、何もないか。
Nothing here yet, I guess.

124
00:09:38,208 --> 00:09:41,008
店。
Shops.

125
00:09:41,008 --> 00:09:44,208
ちょっといいとこ探そう。
Let's find a good spot.

126
00:09:44,208 --> 00:09:46,508
アルケミスト。
Alchemist.

127
00:09:46,508 --> 00:09:48,508
ファーマー。
Farmer.

128
00:09:48,508 --> 00:09:52,508
ここか。
Here it is.

129
00:09:52,508 --> 00:09:56,508
あ、英語になってるの助かる。
Oh, it's in English. That helps.

130
00:09:56,508 --> 00:10:00,008
助かる。読めないから。
That really helps, because I can't read Japanese.

131
00:10:00,016 --> 00:10:01,316
あー、ね。
Ah, I see.

132
00:10:02,316 --> 00:10:05,416
じゃ、な、何、何かをやるのがいいかな？
Well, what... what is it better to do?

133
00:10:08,516 --> 00:10:10,516
じゃ、すーは、ま、一旦...
So, Su will, well, for now...

134
00:10:10,516 --> 00:10:12,316
え、マジどうしたらいいんだ？
Wait, what should I seriously do?

135
00:10:12,316 --> 00:10:14,516
え、本当に何も分かってない...
Wait, I really don't understand anything...

136
00:10:18,516 --> 00:10:23,216
これって、普通で、こう...こうしてもいいんですよね？
You can just do this normally, right?

137
00:10:24,216 --> 00:10:27,216
普通のマイクラの...
Like in normal Minecraft...

138
00:10:29,016 --> 00:10:33,216
ことかな？
...I guess?

139
00:10:36,516 --> 00:10:37,716
バッグ？
Bag?

140
00:10:37,716 --> 00:10:38,816
あ。
Ah.

141
00:10:41,216 --> 00:10:43,016
あ、Equipment slots.
Ah, Equipment slots.

142
00:10:43,216 --> 00:10:44,516
いや、何もない。
No, there's nothing.

143
00:10:47,016 --> 00:10:49,816
ご...5円。
Fi... 5 yen.

144
00:10:50,016 --> 00:10:51,216
お。
Oh.

145
00:10:51,516 --> 00:10:52,516
お。
Oh.

146
00:10:54,016 --> 00:10:55,216
いいじゃん。
Nice.

147
00:10:59,516 --> 00:11:01,216
木、木が欲しい。
Wood, I want some wood.

148
00:11:21,016 --> 00:11:24,016
So basically, to explain to the English viewers, I guess...

149
00:11:24,016 --> 00:11:27,216
...since, I guess, I'm the only English speaking member right now,

150
00:11:29,216 --> 00:11:31,016
anything you do,

151
00:11:31,016 --> 00:11:34,016
like collect and stuff, gives you...

152
00:11:34,016 --> 00:11:35,216
...money.

153
00:11:38,216 --> 00:11:41,216
There's three jobs and one sub-job. Sub-job is the...

154
00:11:41,816 --> 00:11:43,216
...gambler.

155
00:11:47,016 --> 00:11:48,216
And...

156
00:11:58,216 --> 00:12:01,016
Ah, I wonder if it would have been best if I actually went...

157
00:12:01,016 --> 00:12:04,216
...Alchemist for all of the mining stuff first,

158
00:12:04,816 --> 00:12:08,016
and then set up my... set up a little base,

159
00:12:13,216 --> 00:12:15,516
and then start farming, if you know what I mean.

160
00:12:16,016 --> 00:12:17,016
ね？
Right?

161
00:12:20,016 --> 00:12:22,516
最初は、アルケミストが良かったかもな。
Maybe Alchemist would have been better at first.

162
00:12:24,016 --> 00:12:27,216
ま、今日は何回でも代われるから、
Well, since we can change as many times as we want today...

163
00:12:28,016 --> 00:12:29,516
いいかも。
...it should be fine.

164
00:12:30,816 --> 00:12:33,216
So, I think on the first day,

165
00:12:33,216 --> 00:12:36,516
you can basically change anytime you want.

166
00:12:41,016 --> 00:12:42,016
だから...
So...

167
00:12:42,016 --> 00:12:45,016
アルケミスト始めて、ちょっと家とか作れたら
If I start as Alchemist and can build a house or something...

168
00:12:45,016 --> 00:12:47,516
ファーマーになるのがいいかも。
...then maybe it's better to become a Farmer.

169
00:12:53,016 --> 00:12:54,816
ウナ、ウナゴールド的な...
Something like Una, Una Gold...

170
00:12:55,016 --> 00:12:56,516
え？
Eh?

171
00:12:56,516 --> 00:12:57,516
うん、うん。
Yeah, yeah.

172
00:12:58,516 --> 00:12:59,516
はい。
Yes.

173
00:13:00,016 --> 00:13:03,216
で、じゃあ、その錬金アイテム、どこで手に入れるねん？ってなったら、
And then, "where do I get those Alchemy items?" you might ask...

174
00:13:03,216 --> 00:13:09,016
怪しげな砂っていうものがあって、ダンジョンの中だったり、なんか砂漠とかにあったりして、
There's this thing called "Suspicious Sand" inside dungeons or in the desert...

175
00:13:09,016 --> 00:13:09,816
おお。
Oh.

176
00:13:10,016 --> 00:13:12,016
で、なんか、こういうね...
And like, this kind of...

177
00:13:24,016 --> 00:13:26,516
ご、ごえん...
Five, five yen...

178
00:13:29,216 --> 00:13:30,816
じゃなくて、
No, wait...

179
00:13:31,016 --> 00:13:34,016
ご、ご、ゴールド？
G-G-Gold?

180
00:13:34,016 --> 00:13:36,216
Cause it's go, go...

181
00:13:40,016 --> 00:13:41,516
すみません。
Sorry.

182
00:13:44,816 --> 00:13:45,816
で、
So,

183
00:13:47,016 --> 00:13:50,016
いや、やっぱりこれがいいかな？
Well, maybe this is better?

184
00:13:51,016 --> 00:13:54,016
念のため...
Just in case...

185
00:13:56,216 --> 00:14:00,016
これも作ってもいいかも。
Maybe I should craft this too.

186
00:14:07,016 --> 00:14:08,016
え、早く...
I want to get...

187
00:14:08,016 --> 00:14:12,016
あれが欲しいんだよな。
...that thing soon.

188
00:14:12,016 --> 00:14:14,016
あれと言うと...
By "that thing," I mean...

189
00:14:16,016 --> 00:14:18,016
あれだよ。
...that thing.

190
00:14:22,016 --> 00:14:23,516
あれなんです。
That's what it is.

191
00:14:24,016 --> 00:14:25,516
知ってますか？
Do you know?

192
00:14:26,016 --> 00:14:27,516
何と言うか、
What should I call it?

193
00:14:27,516 --> 00:14:28,816
何だか、
Or like...

194
00:14:30,016 --> 00:14:32,516
え、え、日本語難しいな。
Uh, Japanese is hard.

195
00:14:35,016 --> 00:14:36,516
知ってるか？
Do you know?

196
00:14:37,016 --> 00:14:38,216
知ってない？
You don't?

197
00:14:39,016 --> 00:14:41,016
分かんない。
I don't know.

198
00:14:42,016 --> 00:14:44,016
あれですよ、あれ。
It's that thing, that thing.

199
00:14:47,016 --> 00:14:49,016
あれが大事なんですよ。
That thing is important.

200
00:15:00,224 --> 00:15:02,124
あ、迷う
Ah, I might get lost.

201
00:15:07,124 --> 00:15:08,524
11
Eleven.

202
00:15:09,524 --> 00:15:11,024
12
Twelve.

203
00:15:11,524 --> 00:15:14,024
13
Thirteen.

204
00:15:14,324 --> 00:15:16,024
いいぞ、いいぞ
Nice, nice.

205
00:15:28,924 --> 00:15:32,524
木は大事
Trees are important.

206
00:15:42,524 --> 00:15:46,524
このシチュエーションの...
In this situation...

207
00:15:46,524 --> 00:15:49,024
キーになるかも
...it might be key.

208
00:15:49,024 --> 00:15:51,524
知らんけど
I don't know, though.

209
00:15:56,524 --> 00:15:58,524
24
Twenty-four.

210
00:16:15,524 --> 00:16:18,524
あ、りんご
Oh, an apple!

211
00:16:22,024 --> 00:16:25,524
いや、最近日本暑くないですか？
Wait, hasn't Japan been hot lately?

212
00:16:25,524 --> 00:16:30,024
ちょっと涼しくなったかも...
Maybe it's gotten a bit cooler...

213
00:16:30,024 --> 00:16:33,524
なあ？
...right?

214
00:16:38,024 --> 00:16:40,024
なーあ？
Right?

215
00:16:49,524 --> 00:16:54,024
あ、あ、もう夜になっていく
Ah, ah, it's already turning into night.

216
00:16:54,024 --> 00:16:57,024
どうしよう、家作る？
What should I do? Should I build a house?

217
00:17:01,024 --> 00:17:05,024
でも、どこが良いか分かんない
But I don't know where a good place is.

218
00:17:05,524 --> 00:17:07,524
まず...
First...

219
00:17:09,524 --> 00:17:12,024
ボート
...a boat.

220
00:17:12,024 --> 00:17:14,024
作れない？
Can't I make one?

221
00:17:19,024 --> 00:17:22,024
何だっけ？
What was it again?

222
00:17:24,024 --> 00:17:26,524
家欲しい
I want a house.

223
00:17:27,524 --> 00:17:29,024
あ
Ah.

224
00:17:30,524 --> 00:17:34,024
サンキュー、サンキュー。脳内の声
Thank you, thank you. Voices in my head.

225
00:17:38,024 --> 00:17:42,524
え、これですね、ボート
Ah, this is it, a boat.

226
00:17:44,524 --> 00:17:48,524
え、え、え、怖い、怖い
Ah, ah, ah, I'm scared, I'm scared.

227
00:17:50,024 --> 00:17:52,524
どうしよう
What should I do?

228
00:17:53,024 --> 00:17:55,024
ここで作る？
Should I build it here?

229
00:17:55,524 --> 00:17:58,024
作っても良い？
Is it okay if I build it?

230
00:17:59,524 --> 00:18:01,024
あ
Ah.

231
00:18:05,024 --> 00:18:08,524
作っても良いぞ
I can build it.

232
00:18:26,024 --> 00:18:31,024
いや、待とう。そんなに要らないかな？
Wait, let's hold on. Do I really need that much?

233
00:18:39,024 --> 00:18:45,024
そんなに要らないかも
Maybe I don't need that much.

234
00:18:56,524 --> 00:18:59,024
で
And...

235
00:19:03,524 --> 00:19:05,024
ボタン先輩！
Botan-senpai!

236
00:19:06,524 --> 00:19:09,524
えっと、こうして...
Let's see, do this...

237
00:19:11,024 --> 00:19:15,024
いや、でも、なんかゾンビとか見えないかも？
But wait, maybe there aren't any zombies around?

238
00:19:15,024 --> 00:19:18,024
大丈夫？
Is it safe?

239
00:19:18,024 --> 00:19:20,024
かな？
Maybe?

240
00:19:35,024 --> 00:19:38,024
大丈夫？
Is it safe?

241
00:19:38,524 --> 00:19:44,024
いや、でも怖いんだもん。死にたくないんだもん。
But I'm scared. I don't want to die.

242
00:19:50,024 --> 00:19:53,024
大丈夫かも。
Maybe it's safe.

243
00:19:53,024 --> 00:19:59,024
いや、でも家はあった方が良いかもな。
But actually, it might be better to have a house.

244
00:20:12,532 --> 00:20:14,032
ん？
Hm?

245
00:20:30,932 --> 00:20:34,032
え... どこだろう？ My crafting table...
Eh... where is it? My crafting table...

246
00:20:34,032 --> 00:20:39,532
どこ？どこだっけ？ あ、ここか。
Where? Where was it? Ah, here.

247
00:20:50,032 --> 00:20:51,532
えい。
There.

248
00:20:53,032 --> 00:20:56,532
で、家はドアが必要なんです。
And, houses need doors.

249
00:21:10,532 --> 00:21:16,032
ここ、いなの... スタジオ... アパート。
This is Ina's... studio... apartment.

250
00:21:19,532 --> 00:21:21,532
よし、もう一個作ろう。
Alright, let's make one more.

251
00:21:24,032 --> 00:21:26,532
いいんじゃないですか？
Isn't this good?

252
00:21:27,032 --> 00:21:34,032
ちょっと暗いんですけど、いなはあんまり気にしてないので。
It's a bit dark, but Ina doesn't really mind it.

253
00:21:38,032 --> 00:21:40,532
うん、いいかも。
Yeah, maybe it's fine.

254
00:21:44,232 --> 00:21:46,032
くらうー！
Growl!

255
00:21:46,032 --> 00:21:48,032
うわ！
Whoa!

256
00:21:48,032 --> 00:21:50,832
ハロー、イナ！
Hello, Ina!

257
00:21:50,832 --> 00:21:53,032
ぺこら先輩！
Pekora-senpai!

258
00:21:53,032 --> 00:21:54,832
わあ、暗闇！
Wow, darkness!

259
00:21:54,832 --> 00:21:57,032
ライト！/ うわ！あ！
Light! / Whoa! Ah!

260
00:21:57,032 --> 00:21:59,032
ライト！
Light!

261
00:21:59,032 --> 00:22:01,832
おーいえす、がんばろーね、いなちゃん。
Oh yes, let's do our best, Ina-chan.

262
00:22:01,832 --> 00:22:03,532
センキュー！
Thank you!

263
00:22:03,532 --> 00:22:05,532
オッケー！
Okay!

264
00:22:05,532 --> 00:22:11,832
ぺこ神！ぺこ神！火を...
Pekogod! Pekogod! Fire...

265
00:22:11,832 --> 00:22:16,832
人間に火を... くださいました。
She gave... she gave fire to humans.

266
00:22:18,032 --> 00:22:20,532
ああ...
Ah...

267
00:22:30,532 --> 00:22:32,832
えー、いや、こ、こうしようかな？
Hmm, maybe I should do this?

268
00:22:35,532 --> 00:22:38,032
ええと、あれを作る。
Let's see, I'll make that.

269
00:22:38,032 --> 00:22:44,032
あれと言えば、あれなんですよね。
Speaking of that, it's that.

270
00:22:44,032 --> 00:22:49,032
あの、あれあれ。あれ。これ。これこれこれ。
You know, that one, that one. That. This. This, this, this.

271
00:22:49,832 --> 00:22:52,532
で、まずは...
And first...

272
00:23:01,032 --> 00:23:05,032
いや、なんか... いな、やってるの逆じゃないですか？
Wait, isn't what I'm doing the opposite?

273
00:23:05,032 --> 00:23:10,532
今考えたら、なんかアルケミストになろうと思ったら、ファーマーのことを考えるし。
Thinking about it now, if I wanted to be an alchemist, I'm thinking about being a farmer.

274
00:23:10,532 --> 00:23:20,532
今ちょっとファームを作ろうと思ったら、もうアルケミストじゃん？
Now when I thought of making a farm, I'm already an alchemist?

275
00:23:20,532 --> 00:23:22,532
あ、家か。
Ah, a house?

276
00:23:22,532 --> 00:23:24,032
あ、こんにちは。
Ah, hello.

277
00:23:24,032 --> 00:23:25,532
あ、家？家建てたの？
Ah, a house? Did you build a house?

278
00:23:25,532 --> 00:23:27,532
お疲れ様です。
Good job.

279
00:23:28,532 --> 00:23:30,232
すごい！おうちだ！
Wow, a house!

280
00:23:30,232 --> 00:23:31,532
あ、何にもないんです。
Ah, there's nothing in here.

281
00:23:31,532 --> 00:23:33,532
その発想はなかったな。
I didn't think of that idea.

282
00:23:35,532 --> 00:23:39,032
かわいい！おうち。ご飯がない。
Cute! House... we have no food.

283
00:23:39,032 --> 00:23:40,532
ご飯...
Food...

284
00:23:40,532 --> 00:23:42,032
ご飯。
Food.

285
00:23:42,032 --> 00:23:44,032
これ、もらっちゃダメなんかな？
Is it bad to take this?

286
00:23:44,032 --> 00:23:45,032
これ？
This?

287
00:23:45,032 --> 00:23:47,032
ダメだろ。
That's probably bad.

288
00:23:52,532 --> 00:23:56,032
きたきたきた。
Here they come, here they come.

289
00:23:56,032 --> 00:24:05,532
いや、でも、なんか... アルケミストのことをするためには、ご飯が必要ですね。
But still... to do alchemist things, food is necessary.

290
00:24:05,532 --> 00:24:07,532
そうだ。
That's right.

291
00:24:07,532 --> 00:24:10,032
ご飯大事。
Food is important.

292
00:24:10,032 --> 00:24:13,532
お腹空いた。
I'm hungry.

293
00:24:22,032 --> 00:24:25,032
いや、るーな先輩の声かわいい。
Wait, Luna-senpai's voice is cute.

294
00:24:25,032 --> 00:24:27,532
可愛いな。
So cute.

295
00:24:34,032 --> 00:24:36,532
いや、もっとちょうだい。
No, give me more.

296
00:24:36,532 --> 00:24:39,032
ご飯。
Food.

297
00:24:39,032 --> 00:24:41,532
ご飯...
Food...

298
00:24:43,032 --> 00:24:46,532
ご飯だから... ご...
Because it's food... fo...

299
00:24:46,532 --> 00:24:49,032
ご飯、ご飯...
Food, food...

300
00:25:09,940 --> 00:25:11,540
えーっと...
Um...

301
00:25:15,040 --> 00:25:19,440
いつも考えることなんですけど、なんか、エレベーター乗る時...
This is something I always think about, but like, when riding an elevator...

302
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:23,040
たまたま5階に止まるんじゃないですか。
...and it happens to stop on the 5th floor...

303
00:25:28,140 --> 00:25:32,240
いつも思うんですよ。マネージャーちゃんとかに、
I always think about this. To my manager or someone,

304
00:25:32,240 --> 00:25:35,440
5階に止まったら
if it stops on the 5th floor...

305
00:25:38,840 --> 00:25:42,540
「ごかいです」と言いたかった。
...I wanted to say, "It's a misunderstanding." [Pun: 'Gokai' = 5th floor / Misunderstanding]

306
00:25:42,540 --> 00:25:46,040
でも、どんなシチュエーションであれができるのかまだ、
But I don't know in what kind of situation I can use that yet...

307
00:25:46,040 --> 00:25:51,040
まだ分かんない。今も考えてます。
I still don't know. I'm thinking about it even now.

308
00:26:09,540 --> 00:26:13,940
So, basically, I was trying to explain...

309
00:26:13,940 --> 00:26:18,440
...every time I get on the elevator. Cuz like, the Japanese elevator speaks, right?

310
00:26:18,440 --> 00:26:21,040
And then every time it's like...

311
00:26:25,040 --> 00:26:28,240
...land, stop, at the fifth floor,

312
00:26:28,240 --> 00:26:31,040
it says "Gokai desu."

313
00:26:31,040 --> 00:26:34,940
And then, that's also the same pronunciation as...

314
00:26:34,940 --> 00:26:37,440
..."it's a misunderstanding".

315
00:26:37,440 --> 00:26:43,040
So I'm like, "how can I ever make that joke to like, my manager or something?"

316
00:26:47,340 --> 00:26:51,940
どのタイミングで使えばいいか分かんない。
I don't know at what timing I should use it.

317
00:27:22,040 --> 00:27:24,440
どうですか、今のダジャレ？
How was that pun?

318
00:27:44,840 --> 00:27:47,440
200 Yen already!

319
00:27:48,240 --> 00:27:49,740
I'm rich!

320
00:28:13,240 --> 00:28:15,540
あ、あれが必要だな。
Ah, I need that.

321
00:28:16,840 --> 00:28:20,140
これ日本語で何だろ？あの、これ。
What is this in Japanese? Um, this.

322
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:22,540
Hoe?

323
00:28:23,340 --> 00:28:24,740
Hoe!

324
00:28:37,640 --> 00:28:40,040
く、鍬？
A ho... hoe? [Kuwa]

325
00:28:44,840 --> 00:28:51,040
Oh, yeah, there's achievements and stuff.

326
00:28:53,040 --> 00:28:55,340
鍬、鍬...
Hoe, hoe... [Kuwa, kuwa...]

327
00:28:55,340 --> 00:28:57,940
詳しく教えて！
Tell me more in detail! [Pun: 'Kuwa' (hoe) -> 'Kuwashiku' (in detail)]

328
00:28:58,040 --> 00:29:02,040
ね？ハハッ、ハハッ... すみません、すみません。
Right? Haha, haha... Excuse me, excuse me.

329
00:29:22,540 --> 00:29:28,040
いや、何でこんなことになったか分かんない。
I really don't know why it ended up like this.

330
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:46,440
うん、いいじゃん。
Yeah, looks good.

331
00:29:51,040 --> 00:29:54,840
えー、ご飯ができたら...
Ah, once the food is ready...

332
00:30:02,548 --> 00:30:04,548
あの... あれですね... あれ
That... That's it... that...

333
00:30:08,548 --> 00:30:11,048
あ、なんかショップで...
Oh, maybe at the shop...

334
00:30:11,048 --> 00:30:14,248
あれ買えるかな？あの...
I wonder if I can buy that? Um...

335
00:30:14,248 --> 00:30:18,048
アルケミストのショップはまだ見てない。
I haven't checked out the Alchemist shop yet.

336
00:30:23,048 --> 00:30:25,048
ちょっと行ってみようか。
Let's go check it out.

337
00:30:25,048 --> 00:30:28,548
どこだっけ？あっち？え？
Where was it? That way? Eh?

338
00:30:33,248 --> 00:30:36,548
これで、なんか、昼ご飯食べれるかも。
Maybe I can eat some lunch with this.

339
00:30:36,548 --> 00:30:41,548
1217円持ってるし。
Since I have 1,217 yen.

340
00:30:44,248 --> 00:30:46,548
何で言ってることが違うの？
Why are you saying different things?

341
00:30:49,048 --> 00:30:51,548
そんな殺生...
How cruel...

342
00:30:55,548 --> 00:30:57,548
かわいいな。
So cute.

343
00:31:05,548 --> 00:31:07,048
いいなー。
Nice~

344
00:31:07,048 --> 00:31:09,048
うわぁ！
Whoa!

345
00:31:09,548 --> 00:31:14,248
どう？なんか、分かんないことあったりする？
How's it going? Is there anything you don't understand?

346
00:31:14,248 --> 00:31:16,048
まだ大丈夫です。
I'm still doing okay.

347
00:31:16,048 --> 00:31:18,048
大丈夫？オッケー。なんかあったら呼んでね。
You're okay? Okay. Let me know if you need anything.

348
00:31:18,048 --> 00:31:20,048
ありがとうございます！
Thank you so much!

349
00:31:20,048 --> 00:31:22,048
はーい。あ、じゃあイナにちょっとニンジンあげとくよ。
Okay. Oh, let me give Ina some carrots.

350
00:31:22,048 --> 00:31:23,048
おお！
Oh!

351
00:31:23,048 --> 00:31:25,048
神様！
A god!

352
00:31:26,548 --> 00:31:28,248
ありがとうね、来てくれて。
Thanks for coming over.

353
00:31:28,248 --> 00:31:30,248
いや、こちらこそ、ありがとうございます。
No, thank you for having me.

354
00:31:30,248 --> 00:31:32,048
楽しんでね。
Have fun.

355
00:31:32,048 --> 00:31:34,048
なんか、色々、なんか...
Like, all sorts of things...

356
00:31:34,048 --> 00:31:39,048
なんか今日は私だけが異邦人で...
Somehow, today, since I'm the only foreigner...

357
00:31:39,048 --> 00:31:40,548
あ、本当だ。確かに。
Oh, that's true. Indeed.

358
00:31:40,548 --> 00:31:44,048
なんか、マニュアルも、まあ英語でできて、本当にありがとう。
Thanks so much for making the manual in English too.

359
00:31:44,048 --> 00:31:46,048
こんにちは、イエーイ、先輩！
Hello! Yay, Senpai!

360
00:31:46,048 --> 00:31:48,048
ばんちょー！
Bancho!

361
00:31:48,048 --> 00:31:49,048
冒険行った。
I went on an adventure.

362
00:31:49,048 --> 00:31:50,048
はい、いってらっしゃい。
Alright, take care.

363
00:31:50,048 --> 00:31:53,048
じゃあ、また何かあったら呼んでください。
Well, let us know if you need anything else.

364
00:31:53,048 --> 00:31:54,548
はい、ありがとうございます！
Yes, thank you!

365
00:32:01,548 --> 00:32:07,548
アルケミスト... いや、カタカナは読めてよかった。
Alchemist... Whew, I'm glad I can read Katakana.

366
00:32:08,548 --> 00:32:11,548
ある！え、1000円、高っ！
They have it! Eh, 1,000 yen, so expensive!

367
00:32:14,048 --> 00:32:17,048
高い！高い！
Expensive! Expensive!

368
00:32:20,048 --> 00:32:22,048
買う？
Should I buy it?

369
00:32:23,048 --> 00:32:26,548
お、500円...
Oh, 500 yen...

370
00:32:28,048 --> 00:32:34,548
いや、でも、選ばないと...
No, but, I have to choose...

371
00:32:35,048 --> 00:32:37,048
うわぁー！嘘でしょ！
Whoa! No way!

372
00:32:39,048 --> 00:32:41,048
え、選ばないと。
I have to choose.

373
00:32:41,048 --> 00:32:44,048
これ、ピックを買って...
I'll buy a pick...

374
00:32:45,048 --> 00:32:48,048
うん、ピックを買って、釜は作る？...
Yeah, buy a pick, and craft the cauldron?

375
00:32:48,048 --> 00:32:53,048
氷がない、氷がない。もう一回あれ、あれに行こうかな。
No ice, no ice. Should I go back there again?

376
00:32:57,048 --> 00:33:01,048
これもっと安く買える？買えるのかな？
Can I buy this cheaper? I wonder if I can?

377
00:33:14,548 --> 00:33:19,048
あ、違う。違う。
Ah, wait, that's not it. That's not it.

378
00:33:21,048 --> 00:33:26,048
